Believe in yourself, your uniqueness, your worthiness.

I believe we each have this special unique quality. 

The tools of yoga and the process we allow on the mat help us uncover, reveal and align with what feels like our true purpose. 

Authenticity.

It is my hope that through this practice we become closer to ourselves and therefore closer to finding out what our meaningful contribution to humanity is. 

All that on the mat?

Yes. 

The second half of this journey is dynamic and really fun. Keep showing up, keep doing your best, trust your authenticity and Find What Feels Good.

Adriene, I can't thank you enough. I have practiced with you for 75 consecutive days, starting with Home, then Dedicate, and now True. I hope to work my way through all of your 30 day programs and then try them for a second time to round out a full year of daily at-home-yoga. I realized I'm not coming back each day because I set the goal to practice for one whole year. In fact, that was never my intention. I've realized over the past 75 days that I'm coming back each day because it is a gift that I get to return to myself, my center, my mat - a place that I felt so far from for so long. And because of this gift I am finding a sense of peace, an ease from anxiety, and love in coming back to my true self. Thank you, thank you <3

AFTER yesterday's LISTEN journey, I was thinking we were really going to be pushed for today, with a lot of planking and a lot of downward dog (I must say, I never look at my dogs the same as I can see the Yogi within them) but it wasn't so - and I didn't mind.

Once again I came to the mat, totally prepared for something new and something challenging but rewarding at the end and as usual, I was not disappointed.

I really love "coming to the mountain" and so today I was in a really good place from beginning to end although most of my thinking was about, which foot is left and which one is right.  I always lose sight of what foot I am suppose to be on (but I don't care) and as always it was a really nice way to connect with myself after a day of talking to a mediator who is helping me through some personal issues  It was nice to push the session to the back of my mind and step onto the mat and do something that I believe is benefiting me from day to day.  

If I wasn't taking the time to do this, I am sure that I would be looking further into trying to understand what is causing me to feel the way I do and not looking at ways of helping myself through my depression journey.  By letting go of what I am feeling and concentrating on what I am doing on the mat is really helping me through the days.  Once I have finished on the mat, I am in a better frame of mind and I am looking to do something that makes me feel as good.

I have noticed too, that I spend a lot of time yawning while doing yoga.  Is this natural?  I am saying yes, because I feel as though I am winding down after a long day, even if I am doing the yoga in the morning or afternoon or early evening.  Today, I felt tired afterwards, that I took the time to have a rest and I did go to sleep.  Yesterday, I was yawning but I wasn't at the stage of needing sleep.  I am finding this all so relaxing that I have found a good path for when the day gets hard and I just need a little time to myself.  What am I going to do when the 30 days is up is beyond me, but in the mean time, I will continue through to day 30 and I look forward to the times we go to the mountain, we stand in warrior pose and we breathe together.

Hi Adriene! I've been using your videos for near-daily home practice for a couple of years now, but I really wanted to thank you especially for the True series. The Center practice was really pivotal for me and I've already noticed how I hold myself differently. I'm a fairly fit women in my early twenties so I can power through some harder practices, but some easier things still felt a bit weird. Halfway lift never did anything for me until you prompted us to move from our center. Suddenly it became a move where I could expand and feel confident and now I always smile when I lift up. For stronger poses I would enjoy the wobble and burn but now I feel a new strength and ease when holding high lunges and such, and I can feel new muscles in my legs stretching. It's wonderful! Not mention I hold my shoulders further back and my head higher when off the mat. Thank you so much for your dedication to sharing such beautiful practices. Thank you for helping us all find strength we didn't know we had. Namaste x
